    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think we don't have to always dial to target epoch, if `targetEpoch - headBlockEpoch === 1` we can just use the state at `headBlock` thanks to 1 epoch look ahead (the `nextShuffling` in state). Teku had this same optimization https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/7142/files#diff-63983da705fcf1ea1194c2a3e3ee4ede93548b1b7658041bcf9a8d0b47f107b6L73\r\n\r\nit means with `maxSkippedSlot=32` it's most likely we don't have to do epoch transition at all\r\n\r\none edge case is if `headBlock` and `targetEpoch` are in different forks (we're at fork transition) then we should dial to target epoch as specified in https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/4831",
